solution:
Since $AE$ and $AF$ are tangents from the same point to the same circle, $AE = AF$.  Let $x = AE = AF$.  Similarly, let $y = BD = BF$ and $z = CD = CE$.

[asy]
import geometry;

unitsize(2 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, I;

A = (1,2);
B = (0,0);
C = (3,0);
I = incenter(A,B,C);
D = (I + reflect(B,C)*(I))/2;
E = (I + reflect(C,A)*(I))/2;
